    "rationale": "This is a canonical example of the Houben-Hoesch reaction, showing the acylation of an electron-rich aromatic ring (resorcinol) with a nitrile (acetonitrile) under acidic conditions (HCl and a Lewis acid like ZnCl2) to form an aryl ketone (2,4-dihydroxyacetophenone). The reactants and product are simple, acyclic where possible, and clearly illustrate the core transformation of this named reaction.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "This example uses a simple, electron-rich phenol (resorcinol) and a simple nitrile (acetonitrile). It avoids using more complex or generic arenes that could overlap with Friedel-Crafts acylation. It also avoids motifs common in other named reactions like diazo groups, ring expansions, or radical chemistry, ensuring it is specific to the Houben-Hoesch synthesis."
